Guidance for AI assistants (and humans) working in this repo. Keep it short; the detail lives
in [`docs/`](docs/). Start there before non-trivial work.

## Always

- **Commit after every small fix or task.** One logical change per commit,
  [Conventional Commits](CONTRIBUTING.md), imperative summary. Small commits beat big ones.
- **Two long-lived branches.** Feature work integrates on `{{BASE_BRANCH}}`; `{{BASE_BRANCH}}`
  is promoted to the always-deployable `{{MAIN_BRANCH}}` via a periodic release PR. Never merge
  a feature branch straight into `{{MAIN_BRANCH}}`. See
  [`docs/engineering/git-workflow.md`](docs/engineering/git-workflow.md).
- **One directory per branch (worktrees).** Never commit directly to `{{BASE_BRANCH}}` or
  `{{MAIN_BRANCH}}`. Create each task's branch as its own worktree with
  `{{WT_CMD}} new <type>/<slug>` (e.g. `{{WT_CMD}} new fix/scroll-jitter`), which branches off
  `{{BASE_BRANCH}}`, and do all work inside the printed worktree path. The main clone stays on
  `{{MAIN_BRANCH}}` - never `git checkout` a feature branch in it, so parallel sessions never
  collide. Clean up merged worktrees with `{{WT_CMD}} gc`.
- **Follow the task lifecycle.** A request like "do task X from the backlog" means: fetch,
  create the worktree (off `{{BASE_BRANCH}}`), work in small commits, run the quality gate,
  push, open a PR into `{{BASE_BRANCH}}` (referencing the task), then hand the PR off to be
  reviewed and merged. Never self-merge.
- **Fetch before starting work.** `git fetch` at the start of a session and before creating a
  new branch, so you have the latest state from remote.
- **English** in code, comments, docs, commits. {{COPY_LANGUAGE_NOTE}}
- **No emojis, no fancy dashes** anywhere. Regular hyphen `-` only.
- **Docs + `CHANGELOG.md` change in the same PR** as the code they describe. Update only the
  docs relevant to your change.

